00:07:43.300 --> 00:07:46.000
You argue that this gets
to the heart of the problem

00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:48.520
with globalization, which is
obviously under a lot of stress

00:07:48.520 --> 00:07:49.130
today, right?

00:07:49.130 --> 00:07:51.060
It's not working
for a lot of people.

00:07:51.060 --> 00:07:54.409
And we don't think of it as,
well, globalization's bad.

00:07:54.409 --> 00:07:56.200
We think of it as,
globalization's actually

00:07:56.200 --> 00:07:56.910
incomplete.

00:07:56.910 --> 00:07:58.410
Until you have an
internet of value,

00:07:58.410 --> 00:08:00.340
you really can't have
true globalization.

00:08:00.340 --> 00:08:03.636
You need these three core
interoperability technologies

00:08:03.636 --> 00:08:04.510
working all together.

00:08:04.510 --> 00:08:08.300
You need interoperability of
data, of goods, and money,

00:08:08.300 --> 00:08:08.800
right?

00:08:08.800 --> 00:08:12.390
So the world today, of course,
has interoperability of data.

00:08:12.390 --> 00:08:15.890
It's completely transformed the
world over the last 20 years.

00:08:15.890 --> 00:08:19.180
It has interoperability and
goods through a simple thing

00:08:19.180 --> 00:08:21.010
called the shipping container--

00:08:21.010 --> 00:08:23.710
which, before that was
invented, shipping stuff

00:08:23.710 --> 00:08:26.139
was incredibly inefficient
and labor-intensive.

00:08:26.139 --> 00:08:27.430
Stuff would arrive at one port.

00:08:27.430 --> 00:08:29.940
It to be ripped
apart and reshipped.

00:08:29.940 --> 00:08:32.891
With a shipping container,
your ship to train to truck--

00:08:32.891 --> 00:08:34.890
any port in the world,
you have interoperability

00:08:34.890 --> 00:08:37.179
of goods since the 1950s.

00:08:37.179 --> 00:08:39.429
That's sort of what
internet of value is.

00:08:39.429 --> 00:08:41.620
It's like the shipping
container for value.

00:08:41.620 --> 00:08:43.530
And again, that can't
be a blockchain.

00:08:43.530 --> 00:08:46.780
A blockchain is like a single
shipping company that will--

00:08:46.780 --> 00:08:48.430
you'll max out that
shipping company

00:08:48.430 --> 00:08:51.052
and you'll have a dependency
on that one shipping company.

00:08:51.052 --> 00:08:53.260
A shipping container, you
can create endless shipping

00:08:53.260 --> 00:08:53.870
containers.

00:08:53.870 --> 00:08:57.100
It has no effect on any other
shipping containers deployed.

00:08:57.100 --> 00:08:58.360
That's sort of what ILP--

00:08:58.360 --> 00:09:00.540
almost the ultimate
decentralization.

00:09:00.540 --> 00:09:02.500
So that's kind of how
we're thinking about it.

00:09:02.500 --> 00:09:03.880
